# Machine Learning Internship Tasks

This repository contains a collection of machine learning tasks completed during the ML internship. The project covers the main steps of a practical ML workflow: data preprocessing, supervised learning, unsupervised learning, model evaluation, visualization, and a neural network implementation using TensorFlow/Keras.

## Project Overview

The repository is organized by task level. Each script focuses on one machine learning algorithm or workflow and uses datasets stored inside the `Data Set For Task` directory.

Main topics covered:

- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Feature scaling and categorical encoding
- Regression models
- Classification models
- Clustering
- Model evaluation with accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, confusion matrices, and plots
- Neural network classification with TensorFlow/Keras

## Repository Structure

```text
ML-intern/
|-- Data Set For Task/
|   |-- 1) iris.csv
|   |-- 2) Stock Prices Data Set.csv
|   |-- 3) Sentiment dataset.csv
